# Git commit identity

All commits in this repository must be authored and committed as:

- **Name:** Iman Suherman
- **Email:** iman.suherman@gmail.com

## When creating commits

1. Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` or any Cursor agent co-author trailer.
2. Never commit as `suherman@qantas.com.au` or any other email.
3. If Cursor tries to append a Co-authored-by trailer, remove it before committing.

## Agent workflow

When the user asks you to commit:

- Use author identity `Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>` only.
- Do not pass `--author` with a different email.
- Do not include Co-authored-by lines in commit messages.
- Do not use `--no-verify` to bypass hooks unless the user explicitly requests it.

## Hooks

Run `npm run install-hooks` after clone to install:

- **pre-commit** — rejects commits when `git config user.email` or `user.name` is wrong.
- **commit-msg** — rejects commit messages containing Cursor co-author trailers.
- **post-commit** — amends identity drift and strips stray Cursor co-author lines as a fallback.

## Local git config

```bash
git config user.name "Iman Suherman"
git config user.email "iman.suherman@gmail.com"
```
